tourBios.carHigh:
2013: Played his rookie season on the PGA TOUR in after finishing T22 at the PGA TOUR Qualifying Tournament at PGA West in Palm Springs. Played in 16 events and missed 16 cuts...Also made five Web.com Tour starts and played on the weekend twice, at the Mid-Atlantic Championship (T43) and the Price Cutter Charity Championship (T70).

Amateur: Won the 2009 Minnesota Amateur Match Play Championship...Won the 2010 North-South Amateur...Won the 2011 Minnesota Amateur Championship...Advanced to Match Play at the 2011 U.S. Amateur...Won the 2011 Terra Cotta Championship...Won the individual state championship his junior season and the team state championship his senior season at Minnetonka High School.
tourBios.personal: Stopped playing hockey because his mom didn't like him getting hurt...Favorite golf memory is playing Augusta National with his father...If he were not a golfer, would prefer to be on a SWAT team or member of the Drug Enforcement Agency...Biggest thrill outside of golf was riding along with the St. Paul, Minn., SWAT team...Never shaves the week of an event...Enjoys watching Bryce Harper...Twitter account is @Donaldconstable...Favorite gadget is a Fuzzbuster...Not many people know he would love to be a Navy Seal.
